  "prompt": "Shall I learn springs without learning hibernate?",
  "response": "While learning Hibernate can be beneficial, you can definitely learn and use Spring without Hibernate. Here's a comprehensive breakdown:\n\nSpring Without Hibernate:\n1. Possible Approaches\n- Use JDBC directly with Spring\n- Use Spring Data JPA\n- Use other ORM frameworks\n- Use Spring JDBC Template\n\n2. Recommended Learning Path\n- Learn Spring Core fundamentals\n- Understand dependency injection\n- Learn Spring Boot basics\n- Learn basic database connectivity\n- Explore JDBC Template\n- Optional: Learn JPA/Hibernate later\n\n3. Benefits of Learning Spring Without Hibernate\n- Understand core Spring concepts\n- Learn lightweight database operations\n- Develop simpler applications\n- Quicker initial learning curve\n\n4. When to Consider Hibernate\n- Complex database interactions\n- Large enterprise applications\n- Need for advanced ORM features\n- Object-relational mapping requirements\n\n5. Alternative ORM Options\n- MyBatis\n- EclipseLink\n- JPA implementations\n- Spring Data JPA\n\nRecommendation:\n- Start with Spring Core\n- Learn basic database operations\n- Gradually introduce ORM concepts\n- Don't feel pressured to learn Hibernate immediately\n\nBottom line: You can absolutely learn and use Spring without Hibernate!",
